HIV/Spin: China ta ba da rahoton karuwar sabbin cututtuka da kashi 14%
Kasar Sin ta ruwaito cewa yawan mutanen da ke da cutar HIV da kuma cutar spina bifida ya karu da kashi 14 cikin dari.
Hukumar kiwon lafiya ta kasar ta ce mutane fiye da dubu 820 ne ke fama da cutar.
A cikin kwata na biyu na 2018 kadai, an samu sabbin mutane kusan 40 000.
Yawancin sababbin cututtuka sun samo asali ne daga jima'i, wanda ya nuna canji daga baya.
A al'adance, cutar HIV tana yaduwa cikin sauri a wasu sassan kasar Sin sakamakon zubar da jinin da ke dauke da cutar.
Amma adadin mutanen da suka kamu da cutar HIV ta wannan hanyar ya ragu zuwa kusan babu, in ji hukumar lafiya ta kasar Sin a wani taron da aka gudanar a lardin Yunnan.
Duk da haka, kowace shekara, adadin mutanen da ke da cutar HIV da kuma ciwon daji a China yana ƙaruwa da dubu ɗari.
Cutar HIV ta hanyar jima'i babbar matsala ce a cikin al'ummar LGBT a kasar Sin.
A shekara ta 1997, an yi wa luwadi yancin yin aiki a kasar Sin, amma nuna bambanci ga mutanen da ke cikin al'ummar LGBT ya zama ruwan dare gama gari.
Bincike ya nuna cewa domin dabi'u masu ra'ayin mazan jiya, kashi 70 zuwa 90 cikin 100 na maza da suka yi jima'i da maza, a ƙarshe za su auri mata.
Yawancin cututtukan da ake yadawa suna faruwa ne saboda rashin kariya a cikin waɗannan alaƙar.
A shekara ta 2003, gwamnatin kasar Sin ta yi alkawarin samar da magungunan cutar HIV ga kowa a kasar, a matsayin wani bangare na kokarin magance matsalar.
